item.description:
&gt;In the last month, I have been working on a rails3 app and I ran across this interesting problem where I need to create a href link to a another page from my current page.
In my view i have written &lt;%= &ldquo;Please click on this link #{link_to(&lsquo;here&rsquo;, new_house_path)}&rdquo; %&gt;
And interestingly this is displayed as Please click on this link &lt;a href=&ldquo;http://localhost:3000/houses/new&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;
on the front end.
Hours of frustration and google searches leads me to doing this: &lt;%= (&ldquo;Please click on this link #{link_to(&lsquo;here&rsquo;, new_house_path)}&ldquo;).
